io.scanbot.sdk.ui.view.multiple_objects

Class MultipleObjectsDetectorActivity

  • BaseActivity
    • io.scanbot.sdk.ui.view.multiple_objects.MultipleObjectsDetectorActivity

  • public class MultipleObjectsDetectorActivity
extends BaseActivity

    Encapsulates all logic for multiple object detection in one RTU component.

    Can be started using Activity.startActivityForResult with Intent from MultipleObjectsDetectorActivity.newIntent - note the requestCode passed.

    Override Activity.onActivityResult and look for noted requestCode.

    Obtain detection result using MultipleObjectsDetectorActivity.parseActivityResult method.

    Also see class MultipleObjectsDetectorConfiguration, RESULT_LICENSE_INVALID

    See Also:
    Activity.startActivityForResult, Intent, MultipleObjectsDetectorActivity.newIntent, Activity.onActivityResult, MultipleObjectsDetectorActivity.parseActivityResult, class MultipleObjectsDetectorConfiguration

      • parseActivityResult

        @JvmStatic
 @NotNull
public static java.util.List<io.scanbot.sdk.persistence.Page> parseActivityResult(@Nullable
                                                                                                       android.content.Intent data)

        Use this to obtain detection results from Intent object - the one given in Activity.onActivityResult method.

        Example:

        if (requestCode == CAMERA_MULTIPLE_DETECTOR_REQUEST_CODE && resultCode == Activity.RESULT_OK) {
  val multipleDetectorResult = MultipleObjectsDetectorActivity.parseActivityResult(data)

  if (multipleDetectorResult.isEmpty()) {
     Toast.makeText(this@MyCurrentActivity, "No result was set or nothing detected", Toast.LENGTH_LONG).show()
  } else {
     startActivity(MyAwesomeActivity.newIntent(this@MyCurrentActivity, multipleDetectorResult))
  }
}

        See Also:
        Intent, Activity.onActivityResult
